<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Akili_Lifebringer:
[B]Here are answers based on what I do and have seen done. 

1. Since there will be multiple clerics there obviously and multiple groups. I imagine there will be a main tank who will take most of the damage and will hold agro as long as people arent attacking before the tank has assumed agro. If your not in the Main Tanks group then heal your group and make a hotkey to target the main tank to assist in healing or what not. I also usually make a hotkey to target the enchanters on the raid to help keep them alive as well. 

2. I wouldnt worry to much about resist gear for the planes unless you plan on doing the Mini Bosses there and then you would need Cold resists and magic resists. But unless you have a pretty strong guild I doubt you will do these. Naggy/Vox you definately need resist gear. Get Magic Resist as high as you can. 

3. I keep my tanks fully buffed with all including Symbol, I keep myself and my enchanter full buffed, most other classes shouldnt be getting hit often since there SHOULD be a main tank that is getting the agro, so I give them My lower end Symbol as well as AC and whatever AC/HP buff you have for your level. If you have an enchanter with clarity 2 and someone is providing the gems for the raid it doesnt hurt to keep everyone fully buffed especially if you are all basically under level 55.  Dont worry to much about resists in fear.

4. There are a few mobs that debuff everyone near them when they are pulled. Make sure you stay out range of these as should all the casters so you dont have to constantly rebuff them. Make sure your atleast a bubble into 46 before you go also. 

Good luck on your raid and dont be to frusterated if you die several times as it is bound to happen. Most of all Have fun!

Akili Lifebringer
57th Templar 
Valorguard/The Nameless
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
